'''Dr. Doyin Okupe''' was the Senior Special Assistant on Public Affairs to former President [[Goodluck Jonathan (2010 - 2015) ]] of Nigeria.<ref>{{cite news|title=Okupe appointed Jonathan’s adviser|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/okupe-appointed-jonathans-adviser/|accessdate=26 April 2014|newspaper=Punch Newspaper|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426214756/http://www.punchng.com/news/okupe-appointed-jonathans-adviser/|archivedate=26 April 2014|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Jonathan appoints Okupe SSA Public Affairs|url=http://dailyindependentnig.com/2012/07/jonathan-appoints-okupe-ssa-public-affairs/|accessdate=26 April 2014|newspaper=Daily Independent|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426202155/http://dailyindependentnig.com/2012/07/jonathan-appoints-okupe-ssa-public-affairs/|archivedate=26 April 2014|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=PDP, ACN bicker over Okupe|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2012/08/pdp-acn-bicker-over-okupe/|accessdate=26 April 2014|newspaper=Vanguard Newspaper}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Jonathan Appoints Okupe Aide|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/jonathan-appoints-okupe-aide/120938/|accessdate=26 April 2014|newspaper=ThisDay Live|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426201055/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/jonathan-appoints-okupe-aide/120938/|archivedate=26 April 2014|df=}}</ref> Before his recent appointment by President Jonathan in 2012, Okupe was spokesman for former President [[Olusegun Obasanjo]] and a former governorship aspirant of the Peoples Democratic Party in Ogun State in 2003.<ref>{{cite news|title=Okupe appointed Jonathan’s adviser|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/okupe-appointed-jonathans-adviser/|accessdate=26 April 2014|newspaper=Punch Newspaper|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426214756/http://www.punchng.com/news/okupe-appointed-jonathans-adviser/|archivedate=26 April 2014|df=}}</ref>

